FrmAndLnRfrncDsc: Part I: Additional Information
ExplntnTxt: NEC is broadly supported in nature and is deemed to meet the 33 1/3% support public support test under current guidance. Since NEC uses the special rule based on meeting the 33 1/3% support test on Schedule B, NEC is required to disclose the Part II. Support Schedule for Organizations Described in Sections 170(b)(1)(A)(iv) and 170(b)(1)(A)(vi). However, due to a Form 990 software limitation, NEC is unable to both disclose Part II in Schedule A and check off line 2 of Part I, for schools in Schedule A and to have Schedule E completed. This software limitation only allows the organization to enter Part II of Schedule A if one of the boxes on lines 5, 7, or 8 of Part I is checked off or if the organization failed to qualify under Part III of Schedule A. This software limitation also only allows the organization to enter Schedule E if the organization checks off line 2 of Schedule A, Part I. The public support percentages were 73.31% and 66.25% for 2016 (Schedule A, Part II, Section C, Line 14) and 2015 (Schedule A, Part II, Section C, Line 15), respectively. The complete calculation is available upon request.

ExplntnTxt: MILLIGAN COLLEGE RECEIVED AN IRS DETERMINATION LETTER APRIL 3, 1947 STATING THAT THE ORGANIZATION WAS RECOGNIZED AS AN ORGANIZATION EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAX UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. ADDITIONALLY, THE ORGANIZATION WAS ALSO DETERMINED NOT TO BE A PRIVATE FOUNDATION AS DEFINED IN SECTION 509(A) OF THE CODE BECAUSE IT WAS AN ORGANIZATION DESCRIBED IN SECTION 509(A)(1) AND SECTION 170(B)(1)(A)(II), WHICH IS IDENTIFIED IN SCHEDULE A, PART I, LINE 2, AS A SCHOOL. IT IS AN EDUCATIONAL ORGANIZATION WHICH NORMALLY MAINTAINS A REGULAR FACULTY AND CURRICULUM AND NORMALLY HAS A REGULARLY ENROLLED BODY OF PUPILS OR STUDENTS IN ATTENDANCE AT THE PLACE WHERE ITS EDUCATIONAL ACTIVITIES ARE REGULARLY CARRIED ON. ExplntnTxt: Rensselaer is a school described in Section 170(b)(1(A)(ii) and checked box 2 on Schedul A, Part I on the current year and previously filed Form 990 returns. Instructions for Form 990, Part IV, line 2 requires an organization to answer "Yes" if it meets the 33 1/3% support test of the requlations under sections 509(a)(1) and 170(b)(1)(A)(vi), checks the box on Schedule A, Part II, line 13, 16a or 16b and received from any one contributor contributions of the greater of $5,000 or 2% of the amount on Part VIII, line 1h. Rensselaer meets this test and have answered "Yes" to Part IV, line 2 which requires completing Schedule B. Furthermore, the instructions states that an organization filing Schedule B can limit the contributors it reports on Schedule B to greater than 2% of the amount on Part VIII, line 1h only if it checks the box on Schedule A, Part II, line 13, 16a or 16b. However, the tax software that Rensslaer uses to prepare the Form 990 will not display Schedule A, Part II when box 2 is checked on Schedule A, Part I. To be compliant with the instructions for Form 990, Part IV, line 2, Rensselaer is submitting the completed Scheduel A, Part II as a separate attachment.

FrmAndLnRfrncDsc: PART I, LINE 12G:
ExplntnTxt: SOMERVILLE HOSPITAL (THE "ORGANIZATION") IS A WHOLLY-OWNED SUBSIDIARY OF THE CAMBRIDGE PUBLIC HEALTH COMMISSION D/B/A CAMBRIDGE HEALTH ALLIANCE (CHA). CHA IS A GOVERNMENT ENTITY CREATED BY, AND CURRENTLY EXISTING PURSUANT TO, MASSACHUSETTS STATUTE, CHAPTER 147 OF THE ACTS AND RESOLVES OF 1996. NOTWITHSTANDING THE ORGANIZATION'S NAME, THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT OPERATE ANY FACILITY THAT IS, OR IS REQUIRED TO BE, LICENSED, REGISTERED, OR SIMILARLY RECOGNIZED BY THE COMMONWEALTH OF MASSACHUSETTS. FACILITIES LOCATED ON REAL PROPERTY OWNED BY THE ORGANIZATION ARE OPERATED BY CHA. THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDES ITS FACILITIES TO CHA AT OR BELOW COST AND LEASES ITS EMPLOYEES TO CHA, SUCH EMPLOYEES BEING UNDER THE DIRECT CONTROL AND SUPERVISION OF CHA. CHA PAYS ALL EXPENSES INCURRED BY THE ORGANIZATION TO OPERATE ITS FACILITIES, INCLUDING THE COSTS OF ALL MAINTENANCE AND CAPITAL IMPROVEMENTS TO THESE FACILITIES. CHA REIMBURSES THE ORGANIZATION FOR LEASED EMPLOYEES AT FAIR MARKET VALUE. PART IV, SECTION A, LINE 2: THE ORGANIZATION'S SOLE SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION IS THE CAMBRIDGE PUBLIC HEALTH COMMISSION D/B/A CAMBRIDGE HEALTH ALLIANCE ("CHA"). CHA DOES NOT HAVE AN IRS DETERMINATION OF STATUS UNDER SECTION 509(A)(1) OR (2) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (THE "CODE") BECAUSE IT IS A GOVERNMENTAL UNIT. CHA WAS CREATED IN 1996 BY CHAPTER 147 OF THE ACTS OF 1996 OF THE COMMONWEALTH OF MASSACHUSETTS (THE "ENABLING ACT") AS "A BODY POLITIC AND CORPORATE." IN THE ENABLING ACT, THE MASSACHUSETTS LEGISLATURE DECLARED, "[CHA] IS HEREBY CONSTITUTED A PUBLIC INSTRUMENTALITY AND THE EXERCISE BY [CHA] OF THE POWERS CONFERRED BY THIS ACT SHALL BE DEEMED AND HELD TO BE THE PERFORMANCE OF AN ESSENTIAL PUBLIC FUNCTION." THE ENABLING ACT FURTHER PROVIDES THAT CHA IS GOVERNED AND CONTROLLED BY A BOARD APPOINTED BY THE CITY MANAGER OF CAMBRIDGE. CONSEQUENTLY, CHA IS AN ORGANIZATION DESCRIBED IN SECTION 170(B)(1)(A)(V) AND, BY EXTENSION, SECTION 509(A)(1) OF THE CODE. BY LETTER TO THE ORGANIZATION DATED JULY 25, 2013, THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE STATED, "WE DETERMINED THAT YOU ARE A TYPE I SUPPORTING ORGANIZATION UNDER 509(A)(3). A TYPE I SUPPORTING ORGANIZATION IS OPERATED, SUPERVISED, OR CONTROLLED BY ONE OR MORE PUBLICLY SUPPORTED CHARITIES." THERE HAVE BEEN NO CHANGES TO CHA'S OPERATION, SUPERVISION, OR CONTROL OF THE ORGANIZATION SINCE JULY 25, 2013.

Instructions for Form 990, Part IV, line 2 requires an organization to answer "Yes" if it meets the 33 1/3% support test of the requlations under sections 509(a)(1) and 170(b)(1)(A)(vi), checks the box on Schedule A, Part II, line 13, 16a or 16b and received from any one contributor contributions of the greater of $5,000 or 2% of the amount on Part VIII, line 1h. Rensselaer meets this test and have answered "Yes" to Part IV, line 2 which requires completing Schedule B. Furthermore, the instructions states that an organization filing Schedule B can limit the contributors it reports on Schedule B to greater than 2% of the amount on Part VIII, line 1h only if it checks the box on Schedule A, Part II, line 13, 16a or 16b. However, the tax software that Rensslaer uses to prepare the Form 990 will not display Schedule A, Part II when box 2 is checked on Schedule A, Part I. To be compliant with the instructions for Form 990, Part IV, line 2, Rensselaer is submitting the completed Scheduel A, Part II as a separate attachment.

FrmAndLnRfrncDsc: SCHEDULE A, PART IV, SECTION A, LINE 1
ExplntnTxt: MERCY HOSPITAL'S SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION IS NOT LISTED BY NAME IN THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, BUT IS DESIGNATED BY PURPOSE. THE PURPOSE OF MERCY HOSPITAL AS STATED IN ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS IS TO ADVANCE, PROMOTE, SUPPORT, AND CARRY OUT THE PURPOSES OF CATHOLIC HEALTH MINISTRIES AND TRINITY HEALTH. ITS SPECIFIC PURPOSES ARE TO ENGAGE IN THE DELIVERY OF AND TO CARRY ON, SPONSOR OR PARTICIPATE, DIRECTLY OR THROUGH ONE OR MORE AFFILIATES, IN ANY ACTIVITIES RELATED TO THE DELIVERY OF HEALTH CARE AND HEALTH CARE RELATED SERVICES AS APPROPRIATE IN CARRYING OUT THE HEALTH CARE MISSION OF CATHOLIC HEALTH MINISTRIES AND TRINITY HEALTH. SUCH ACTIVITIES INCLUDE THE SUPPORT AND ASSISTANCE OF AFFILIATES TO ACCOMPLISH THE FOREGOING PURPOSES. THE SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION LISTED IN PART I, LINE 12 IS AN AFFILIATE OF TRINITY HEALTH AND QUALIFIES AS A SEC. 509(A)(1) PUBLIC CHARITY, AND SHARES THE EXEMPT PURPOSES OF MERCY HOSPITAL AND TRINITY HEALTH.

FrmAndLnRfrncDsc: SCHEDULE A, PART IV, SECTION A, LINE 2
ExplntnTxt: MERCY HOSPITAL SUPPORTS HOLY CROSS HOSPITAL. HOLY CROSS HOSPITAL DOES NOT HAVE AN IRS DETERMINATION OF STATUS UNDER SECTION 509(A)(1); IT HAS BEEN RECOGNIZED AS EXEMPT UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) UNDER GROUP EXEMPTION NO. 0928 AND IS LISTED IN THE OFFICIAL CATHOLIC DIRECTORY AS A HOSPITAL. HOLY CROSS HOSPITAL IS A PUBLIC CHARITY AS DESCRIBED IN SECTION 509(A)(1) BECAUSE IT IS A HOSPITAL AS DESCRIBED UNDER SECTION 170(B)(1)(A)(III).

FrmAndLnRfrncDsc: SCHEDULE A, PART IV, SECTION C, LINE 1
ExplntnTxt: BOTH MERCY HOSPITAL AND ITS SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION ARE CONTROLLED BY TRINITY HEALTH CORPORATION. TRINITY HEALTH CORPORATION HAS THE POWER TO APPOINT OR ELECT A MAJORITY OF THE BOARDS OF BOTH MERCY HOSPITAL AND ITS SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION.

FrmAndLnRfrncDsc: SCHEDULE A, PART I, LINE 11G(VI)
ExplntnTxt: BEFORE DISCONTINUING OPERATIONS, MERCY HOSPITAL PROVIDED HEALTH CARE SERVICES TO THE COMMUNITY IN FURTHERANCE OF THE CHARITABLE PURPOSE OF ITS SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION AND PARENT ORGANIZATION.

FrmAndLnRfrncDsc: PART IV, SECTION D, LINE 3:
ExplntnTxt: THE SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION HAS A SIGNIFICANT VOICE IN THE ORGANIZATION'S INVESTMENT POLICIES AND IN DIRECTING THE USE OF THE ORGANIZATION'S INCOME OR ASSETS. ALL THREE OF THE REPRESENTATIVES APPOINTED BY THE SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION ARE VOTING MEMBERS OF THE ORGANIZATION'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND PARTICIPATE IN THE DECISION-MAKING PROCESS AT THE HIGHEST LEVEL. IN ADDITION, ONE REPRESENTATIVE OF THE SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION SERVES ON THE FINANCE COMMITTEE, WHICH GENERALLY OVERSEES THE OPERATIONS AND FINANCIAL CONDITION OF THE ORGANIZATION, INCLUDING ITS INVESTMENT POLICIES. TWO REPRESENTATIVES OF THE SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION SERVE ON AN INTERNAL COMMITTEE WHICH MONITORS ADHERENCE TO ANY QUALITATIVE CONTRACTUAL REQUIREMENTS. NO NEW DEBT IS INCURRED BY THE ORGANIZATION WITHOUT THE APPROVAL OF THE SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION. LASTLY, THE SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION IS GIVEN A SIGNIFICANT VOICE IN THE CONDUCT OF THE ORGANIZATION'S AFFAIRS BY VIRTUE OF ITS OPERATING SUBLEASE WITH THE ORGANIZATION.

FrmAndLnRfrncDsc: PART IV, SECTION E, LINE 2A:
ExplntnTxt: THE ORGANIZATION SUPPORTS THE NCMC BOARD OF TRUSTEES BY CONTRACTING WITH BANNER HEALTH (AN ARIZONA 501(C)(3) ORGANIZATION) TO OPERATE THE NORTH COLORADO MEDICAL CENTER. UNDER THE TERMS OF THE CONTRACT, BANNER HEALTH SYSTEM PAYS AN ANNUAL USE CHARGE TO THE ORGANIZATION FOR HOSPITAL FACILITIES, EQUIPMENT AND THE BUSINESS FRANCHISE. THESE FUNDS, TOGETHER WITH OTHER CASH RESERVES, ARE USED BY THE ORGANIZATION TO PROVIDE THE NORTH COLORADO MEDICAL CENTER WITH LIQUID WORKING CAPITAL AND FUNDING FOR MAJOR AND ROUTINE CAPITAL EXPENDITURES. THE ORGANIZATION MAY BORROW MONEY TO FUND CAPITAL PROJECTS, WHICH RESULTS IN THE ORGANIZATION SERVICING THE DEBT INCURRED. IN ADDITION, THE ORGANIZATION ALSO PROVIDES GRANTS TO SUPPORT LOCAL HEALTHCARE CHARITIES. PLEASE SEE SCHEDULE A, PART I, LINE 11G FOR THE AMOUNT OF SUPPORT PROVIDED. THESE ACTIVITIES DIRECTLY FURTHER THE EXEMPT PURPOSE OF THE ORGANIZATION, WHICH IS TO PROVIDE QUALITY HEALTHCARE AT A REASONABLE COST TO THE NORTH COLORADO MEDICAL CENTER SERVICE AREA.

FrmAndLnRfrncDsc: PART IV, SECTION E, LINE 2B:
ExplntnTxt: IF THE ORGANIZATION DID NOT CONDUCT THE ACTIVITIES DESCRIBED IN SECTION E, LINE 2A, THE SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION WOULD HAVE TO DIRECTLY UNDERTAKE THE ACTIVITIES. THE SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION WAS FORMED TO PROVIDE FOR HEALTHCARE NEEDS OF THE REGION, WHICH INCLUDES THE AVAILABILITY OF HOSPITAL FACILITIES. THE SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION IS PROVIDING FOR THE HEALTHCARE NEEDS OF THE REGION THROUGH THE USE OF THE ORGANIZATION AND ITS ACTIVITIES.

THIS HELPS CARRY OUT THE MISSION OF ONE OF ITS CONTROLLING SUPPORTED ORGANIZATIONS. THE TOTAL AMOUNT OF SUPPORT PROVIDED FOR 2017 WAS $4,726.
